   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON EIGHT THE PRACTICE OF</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE LORD'S TABLE MEETING 5 Scripture Reading: Lev 3:3-5, 9-11, 14-17; 7:11-21, 28-34 OUTLINE Presenting Christ as the peace offering to the Father: The portions of the peace offering: To God: From the ox 3:3-5: 1 The fat upon the inwards.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>2 The two kidneys and the fat on them.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>3 The caul net above the liver.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>From the sheep or lamb 3:9-11: 1 The same as from the ox.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>2 Plus the whole fat tail.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>From the goat the same as from the ox 3:14-16.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To the offering priest: One cake as a heave offering unto the Lord 7:14.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The right thigh as a heave offering unto the Lord 7:32-34.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>To all the priests the breast as a wave offering 7:30-31, 34.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To the offerer: The flesh meat of the cattle 7:15-18: 1 Of the peace offering for thanksgiving good for eating on the offering day v. 15.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>2 Of the peace offering for a vow or a voluntary offering good for eating for two days vv.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>16-18.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Cakes 7:12-13: 1 Unleavened cakes thin cakes with holes mingled with oil.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>2 Unleavened, hollow wafers anointed with oil.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>3 Cakes of fine flour saturated and mingled with oil.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>4 Leavened bread.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>To others 7:19-21: The flesh of the cattle.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Cleanness being required.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Focus: Christ as the peace offering offered by us to the Father is for the enjoyment of God and all the parties participating in the worship in the dispensing of God.</S>
   </TEXT>
